    "created_at": "2015-10-24T23:48:23Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-24T23:48:23Z",
    "body": "I believe I've encounter similar behaviour with [an app I'm writing](https://github.com/zz85/space-radar-electron) to scan and visualize disk usage. The way I call [fs.readdir is a simple recursion](https://github.com/zz85/space-radar-electron/blob/master/js/du.js#L18) but if ran within the same renderer process would cause the UI to lock.\n\nI'm not sure if this is causing by any blocking calls, but I suspect that the recursive readdir calls are too too fast that it starves events within the same process. My current workaround to run fs operations in a webview. File information is passed via localStorage or by serializing and deserializing thru file system (it's workable thru ipc, I did this for a speed hack).\n\nJust sharing some of my experiences, and I wrote a little more about the [speed hacks in this issue](https://github.com/zz85/space-radar-electron/issues/6) getting UI not to lock as much as possible.\n"
